# AI Image Generator

## Summary
AiImageGenerator is the main card of the package: a ChatGPT-style image studio. Its data model is deliberately thin — `history = linksToMany(AiImage)` (every generated image is its own card, in generation order), plus the composer defaults `llmModel` (an enum of OpenRouter image models) and `aspectRatio` (AspectRatioField), persisted so the studio remembers your last choices. It sets `prefersWideFormat` and a Sparkles icon. The whole isolated/embedded experience is composed from `./components` rather than written inline, keeping the schema small and instances safe to re-index. The studio offers: a chat-style bottom composer that continues from the latest image or starts a new one; a focused Refine editor with Reprompt (regenerate, may reframe the aspect ratio) and brush-based Paint-area (inpaint, locked to the source framing) modes; a GitLens-style version graph in the sidebar that draws the `parent` lineage as a branch tree (each new image starts its own lane); light/dark theming through the standard semantic-token pipeline; and a Stop control to cancel an in-flight generation. Every generation runs through `GenerateAiImageCommand`, so each result is a fully-recorded AiImage linked into `history`.

## Import
```js
import { AiImageGenerator } from '../ai-image-generator';
```

## Usage
AiImageGenerator is a card, so consuming cards link to it rather than containing it:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksTo } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { AiImageGenerator } from '../ai-image-generator';

export class Project extends CardDef {
  @field imageStudio = linksTo(() => AiImageGenerator);
}
```
New images append to `history` as AiImage cards as the user generates and refines — nothing else needs wiring.

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.imageStudio />
```
Renders the linked studio; open it isolated for the full experience (composer, version tree, refine editor). The embedded/fitted format shows the latest image with a caption.
